{
  "text": "Since no results have been published regarding the multidirectional responses of a pile-raft foundation subjected to both active and passive loads, APPR was first used to calculate the responses of the pile-raft foundation under pure active loads and pure passive loads separately to verified the ability of APPR to evaluate this problem. Then, APPR was used to calculate the responses of a multidirectionally loaded pile-raft foundation subjected to tunnelling and compared with results from FEM. As shown in Figure 8 , the pile-raft foundation was only subjected to an active load combined with a vertical load, a horizontal load, and a moment. In this case (1) where the loads were applied separately and (2) where the loads were applied simultaneously. The results were compared with the results from [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and FEM. It can be seen from Figure 9 , without considering the passive load, that the results from APPR are the same as the results from the method proposed by [CITATION_3] when the loads were applied simultaneously. Moreover, the results from APRR also agree well with the results from [CITATION_4] and FEM. ",
  "correct_citation": {
